===Etymology===
Attested somewhat late, in {{w|Warring States period}}'s texts.

A Southeast Asian area word ([https://core.ac.uk/download/pdf/156628995.pdf Alves 2015]).
* Per {{zh-ref|Schuessler 2007}}, most likely of {{der|zh|aav}} origin. Compare {{cog|mkh-pro|*truŋ||stable, sty, cage}} and {{m|mkh-pro|*kruŋ||to confine}} in [http://sealang.net/monkhmer/dictionary/ Shorto 2006], whence {{cog|km|ទ្រុង||tr=trŭng|cage}}, {{m|km|ក្រុង||tr=krŏng|to confine}}, {{cog|kdt|tr=thrùŋ|t=cage}}, potentially {{cog|vi|chuồng||cage; shed; coop}}, and so forth. The Vietnamese may possibly be an early Chinese loan instead ({{zh-ref|Alves 2018}}).
* STEDT reconstructs {{der|zh|sit-pro|*kruːŋ||cage}}, based on e.g. {{cog|grt|gring||cage}}, {{cog|my|ချိုင့်|tr=hkyuing.}}. Schuessler thinks these were also borrowed from Austroasiatic.
* Other forms include {{cog|tai-pro}}, whence {{cog|th|กรง||tr=grong|cage}}; and {{cog|poz-pro|*kuruŋ}}, whence {{cog|id|kurung||cage}}, {{cog|tl|kulong||caged}}. Schuessler believes these are also ultimately from Austroasiatic.

